    <div class="comment-text editable-message-text" itemprop="commentText"><p>@Tristan,</p>
<p>The OAuth attack scenario is similar to trust one:</p>
<p>* Trustee creates an OAuth authentication delegation (with elevated privs)<br />
* ReAuth with new OAuth based delegation.</p>
<p>Alternatively, someone authenticated with an OAuth delegation could:<br />
* Create Trust with elevated privileges<br />
* ReAuthenticate with new Trust.</p>
<p>The fixes Adam Young has provided eliminate both of these alternate attack vectors.</p></div>
    
    
    
